(596, 69, 2, 'Daily Diary: If you are trialling the powered chair over several days then as well as your feedback about the Obstacle Alerting System we would like you to put information about your medication [optional], wellbeing and where you have been driving throughout the day into an electronic diary. This information will help us to see how the Obstacle Alerting System, your medication, wellbeing and location might influence your driving. Experience from the Stage 1 Trial shows that the information in the Daily Diary is very important in helping us to understand how you are driving. When information has not been provided it is much more difficult to analyse the data. For example if your medication makes you feel sleepy, or if you feel sleepy, then this may affect how you drive. Please note it down. Or if you have more collisions than usual, please note this down too. The more information you record, the more valuable the trial. Therefore although entry of data is quite demanding please make every effort to do so. The diary can be accessed via the tablet to be mounted on your wheelchair. A wireless keyboard may also be provided.', 'Daily Diary: If you are trialling the powered chair over several days then as well as your feedback about the Obstacle Alerting System we would like you to put information about your medication [optional], wellbeing and where you have been driving throughout the day into an electronic diary. This information will help us to see how the Obstacle Alerting System, your medication, wellbeing and location might influence your driving. Experience from the Stage 1 Trial shows that the information in the Daily Diary is very important in helping us to understand how you are driving. When information has not been provided it is much more difficult to analyse the data. For example if your medication makes you feel sleepy, or if you feel sleepy, then this may affect how you drive. Please note it down. Or if you have more collisions than usual, please note this down too. The more information you record, the more valuable the trial. Therefore although entry of data is quite demanding please make every effort to do so. The diary can be accessed via the tablet to be mounted on your wheelchair. A wireless keyboard may also be provided.', 'Daily Diary: If you are trialling the powered chair over several days then as well as your feedback about the Obstacle Alerting System we would like you to put information about your medication [optional], wellbeing and where you have been driving throughout the day into an electronic diary. This information will help us to see how the Obstacle Alerting System, your medication, wellbeing and location might influence your driving. Experience from the Stage 1 Trial shows that the information in the Daily Diary is very important in helping us to understand how you are driving. When information has not been provided it is much more difficult to analyse the data. For example if your medication makes you feel sleepy, or if you feel sleepy, then this may affect how you drive. Please note it down. Or if you have more collisions than usual, please note this down too. The more information you record, the more valuable the trial. Therefore although entry of data is quite demanding please make every effort to do so. The diary can be accessed via the tablet to be mounted on your wheelchair. A wireless keyboard may also be provided.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 11, 0, '2020-10-19 07:32:12.244', '2020-10-19 07:32:12.244', NULL, 3, 3, NULL),
